channel.title: My server isnt applying any changes i make in the java script
channel.description: ok, ive tried doing like 50 diffrent servers and every time i try to make a new one something goes wrong! so i finally deleted ALL the files i had on all the servers and downloaded one single host (svenscap3 PK) and this one when i logged in had all the same exact info as the last server i made.... it had all the changes i made, all the items i had, and EVERYTHING! whats up?? i looked in my "private server" file under programs and it had only the svenscap3 pk files in it.... why is it showing all the old info? and when i go into the .java files and change stuff it does nothing (begin with diff. items exc.) nothing! can someone help me figure out what im doing wrong??? i would be very greatful! ty.

yes, every time i make changes to my .java files i save them… when i run my compiler it works fine… i dont know… well… im pretty ure i found out the prollem… instead of a router i have a motem… hub… i dont know exactly what its calle… but its got 8 ports instead of one… got 3 pc’s running off it… but yeah when i went to do the port forwarding thing my friend said “ooh… dont worry bout it if you dont have a router… ittl work without that…” i guess he was wrong… ill put up another question topic asking if its possible to run one of these servers without a router… i think my chances of being able to learn scripting and server stuff are getting pretty narrow… THIS SUX! lol… but yeah thanks for the help!!!
